  note      = {ADORE / STAR. The crucial nuance that makes a behavioral hard-negative source non-redundant: "static hard negative sampling does not necessarily lead to performance improvements compared with random negative sampling. It improves the top-ranking performance but may harm the recall capability." BM25 Neg almost underperforms Rand Neg on every metric in their experiments. Value comes from dynamically updating the hard-negative set as the model improves — not from mere hardness. Key citation for the argument that mining procedure matters more than mere hardness. DOI from LLM knowledge, re-verify.},
}

